Key Match Events: Steph Curry scored 16 of his 24 points in the second half in his return from an ankle injury.
Buddy Hield scored 20 points, part of another strong contribution from the Golden State bench.
Jordan Poole led Washington with 24 points.
Kyshawn George had 20 points for the Wizards.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Golden State's Steve Kerr coached his 800th game, becoming the 18th coach to reach that milestone with only one team.
